# wranngle/career_architect — minimal gitignore
#
# Keep generated and user-specific career data out of new commits. The public
# repo should ship the pipeline, templates, and examples, not a user's search.
#
# Excluded categories:
#   1. Secrets that would be auto-scanned and burned if public
#   2. Regeneratable build artifacts too large to track usefully
#   3. Transient runtime state (locks, pids) that have no value at rest
#   4. User-layer career data and generated work product

# 1 — Secrets (DO NOT COMMIT)
.env
.env.*

# User layer (see DATA_CONTRACT.md)
cv.md
config/profile.yml
modes/_profile.md
article-digest.md
portals.yml
data/*
reports/
output/
jds/
interview-prep/

# Submit-queue stub is part of the runtime contract (queue-applications.mjs),
# so it's committed as a tracked file even though the surrounding data/ tree
# is user-private. Uses data/* (not data/) so this re-include actually fires —
# git refuses to re-include children of a fully excluded parent directory.
!data/submit-queue.md

# Test fixtures under tests/ legitimately mirror those names — keep them tracked.
!tests/fixtures/**/data/
!tests/fixtures/**/data/**
!tests/fixtures/**/reports/
!tests/fixtures/**/reports/**

# 2 — Regeneratable build artifacts
node_modules/
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.so
*.egg-info/
*.egg

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
.nyc_output/
coverage/

# 3 — Transient runtime state
batch/.batch-state.lock/
batch/batch-runner.pid
batch/.resolved-prompt-*.md
.resolved-prompt-*
.update-dismissed
.update-lock
*.bak
*.tmp
*.temp
career-dashboard

# 4 — Stale per-day artifacts (regeneratable; don't pollute history)
data/ranked-*.tsv

# 5 — Voice-coach provisioning record (per-user agent IDs; written by voice-coach.mjs)
data/voice-coach-agent.json

# TypeScript incremental build cache
*.tsbuildinfo
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# Transient bootstrap files
/logs
/old
